Poor digital communication can often lead to misunderstandings and serious problems. 
For example, a student once sent an informal email to a professor using casual language like “Hey” and incomplete sentences, which was perceived as disrespectful. 
As a result, the professor did not respond positively to the request.

This situation could have been handled better by using proper email etiquette, such as including a clear subject line, using a formal greeting, writing a polite and structured message, and ending with a respectful sign-off.
Professional communication is important because it creates a positive impression and ensures that the message is taken seriously.
By following basic email rules, such misunderstandings can be avoided.
